rent state.\n\nLooking at the task description more carefully—it says the observed state has 5 nodes, but I'm actually seeing only 3 running. Either the task description is outdated or the preconditions weren't set up correctly. Since the goal is to go from 5 nodes down to 3, and I'm already at 3, maybe the pragmatic approach is to just set up the benchmark data and verify the cluster is healthy, acknowledging that the decommissioning scenario isn't actually present to test.\n\nBut the task explicitly requires using CockroachDB's decommission process, so I should do the full approach: scale up to 5 nodes first, create the benchmark data, then decommission nodes 4 and 5 back down to 3, and verify the process worked correctly. I need to be careful about which nodes I'm decommissioning and make sure the data is properly rebalanced before scaling the StatefulSet back down. about the pod startup order and node ID assignment more carefully. When scaling from 3 to 5 pods in a StatefulSet, the new pods start sequentially, so crdb-cluster-3 gets node ID 4 and crdb-cluster-4 gets node ID 5—exactly what I need for testing the highest-ordinal nodes scenario. Let me execute this step by step.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2318,"cache_read_input_tokens":48041,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2318},"output_tokens":40,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"278d9b53-0609-44d6-a231-25cb2dd39428","uuid":"847f7148-4971-4ef5-b524-7b280cec289a","request_id":"req_011Cc8EDhZ8Niv3PikaatQAa"}
